node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parks Project on August 11, 2021.

node.text: Fresh prints and bold colors, just what your summer wardrobe needs. Our newest boxy tees are vintage inspired, 100% cotton, and give back to the Open Outdoors for Kids program with every purchase. Grab the set or mix and match! Now we just have to find room in our closet 🤔 Which set is your favorite? #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.text:
It's that time of the week again! Happy #waterfallwednesday 🌊  @yellowstonenps is known for its geothermal features, but have you seen its waterfalls 😍 Lower Falls in the Grand Canyon of Yellowstone National Park is our favorite, what about yours?

Photo by @tim.muangkeo
📍Photo taken on Crow, Eastern Shoshone, and Cheyenne native lands. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

Notice: While we continue to share photos and stories from the wild lands we love, keep in mind, every park has different opening dates and restrictions. Be sure you are following all local, state, and federal guidelines.

node.text: We know it's only August, but we're big believers in planning ahead! Express your love for parks all year long! Our National Parks 2022 Wall Calendar features illustrations by @wyatthersey of national treasures like Zion, Joshua Tree, and Denali. Tag a park lover who needs this in their life—we won't judge if you tag yourself 😉 #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

Welcome to the land of giants 🌲 @sequoiakingsnps is home to groves of Giant Sequoia (Sequoiadendron giganteum), the world's largest trees by volume. node.accessibility_caption: Canyon views from the summit of Angel's Landing in Zion National Park.

node.text:
Talk about a bird's-eye view 🦅
One of the most popular hikes in @zionnps, Angel's Landing is a strenuous 5.4-mile (8 km) round trip hike that leads to some of the most spectacular views in the canyon. With long drop-offs, steep inclines, and narrow trails, this hike is not for the faint of heart.

Heading out to Zion? Summertime means peak visitation, so be sure to pack your patience and have a backup plan. Need some help? Check out our park finder for additional activities and nearby parks. #findyourpark #radparks #leaveitbetter
